Russia: Russo-Swedish War (1590–1595): The Treaty of Tyavzino was signed. Ingria went to Muscovy.
Philippine: Diocese of Manila raised to an Archbishopric
Colegio de San Ildefonso founded in Cebu
Indonesia: First Dutch expedition to Indonesia sets sail for the East Indies with two hundred and forty-nine men and sixty-four cannons led by Cornelis de Houtman.
Brazil: Anglo–Spanish War: An English military expedition led by James Lancaster captures Recife.
